<m:mo> Δ </m:mo>
<m:mi> t </m:mi>
</m:mrow>
</m:mfrac>
</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</equation></para>
<para id="element-42">If the ratio is evaluated for finite time interval, then the ratio is called average angular acceleration and If the ratio is is evaluated for infinitesimally small period (Δ t →0), then the ratio is called instantaneous angular acceleration. Mathematically, the instantaneous angular acceleration is :
</para>
<para id="element-43"><equation id="equation-43"><m:math display="block">
<m:mtable columnalign="left">
<m:mtr>
<m:mtd>
